Implement a unified diff parser that converts raw patch text into a structured representation suitable for side-by-side rendering.

Parse the unified diff format:
- Detect file headers (`--- a/path` and `+++ b/path`)
- Parse hunk headers (`@@ -old_start,old_count +new_start,new_count @@`)
- Classify lines: context (starts with ` `), addition (starts with `+`), deletion (starts with `-`)

Output data structure per file in the diff:
```
DiffFile { old_path, new_path, hunks: Vec<DiffHunk> }
DiffHunk { old_start, new_start, lines: Vec<DiffLine> }
DiffLine { kind: Context|Add|Delete, content: String }
```

Then produce a side-by-side line mapping:
- Context lines appear on both sides
- Deletions appear on the left only (right side blank)
- Additions appear on the right only (left side blank)
- Adjacent deletion+addition blocks are paired line-by-line

This is a pure data transformation module (`src/diff.rs`) with no plugin API dependencies.